g.text: J2, J3: RUN vs PROGRAM configuration
* Install jumper on J3 in the A16 position
PROGRAM configuration - for writing to the flash chip:
* Move the J3 jumper to the ~OE~ position
* Insert the board into the programmer's ZIF socket, 2 rows away from the top.
Don't close the ZIF clamping lever yet.
* Connect J2 VCC to ZIF pin 32. (*)
* Connect J3 A16 to ZIF pin 2.
have a female end that can slide onto to the J2 & J3 pins,
and a male end that can insert into the ZIF socket.
U1 or U2 or U3: flash memory, 128K x 8, parallel, 5v
If necessary, 256K xxx020 part may be used in place of 128K xxx010 part.
xxx040 part may not be used.
